visual.name: AttributeSlicer
visual.description: This visual is experimental and not actively being developed, only major issues will be addressed. Attribute Slicer lets you filter a dataset on a given column by selecting attribute values of interest. The initial display is a helpful overview that lists the most common values first and shows the overall distribution of values as a horizontal bar chart. Whenever you select an attribute value, it is moved to the list of applied filters and all records containing that value are added to the result set for further analysis.

leftAlignText.description: On to left align item text.

showOptions.description: Should the search box and other options be shown.

horizontal.description: Display the attributes horizontally, rather than vertically

valueColumnWidth.description: The percentage of the width that the value column should take up.

labelDisplayUnits.description: The units to use when displaying values.

labelPrecision.description: The precision to use when displaying values.

overflowValueLabels.description: Allow value text to overflow the bar.

singleSelect.description: Only allow for one item to be selected at a time

brushMode.description: Allow for the drag selecting of attributes

showSelections.description: Will show the selected attributes as tokens

colorMode.description: Determines how the individual bars within the time brush are colored

startColor.description: The start color of the gradient

endColor.description: The end color of the gradient

startValue.description: The value to use as the start value

endValue.description: The value to use as the end value

reverseOrder.description: If enabled, the order of the bars will be reversed
